There should be no dependency on the 1st IP address creation to get the 2nd one created.
Both can be created independently, and the 2nd IP create should verify that the Hypervisor network gets the IP overwritten

This one is to proceed the flow (creating the second ip) after assuring that there is already one ip created, and then when the second ip is successully created, we would be checking if the first ip has been overwaritten,
Here probably you can also expect that the IP address is all zeros

This cannot be right
The deleteIP method just deletes the ipaddress and the object from the local copy (addrs).
Then this test would be checking if the addrs contain the same ip after deletion
Please add a comment here saying why do you need to delete the object and then add the user supplied ip again
